<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[667,1194,416,1391]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">
COMMENTS: In the original description, Rothschild said that the form was ‘‘named after Henry Palmer’s companion, who shot the only specimen at present known.’’ The date of collection on the label and the one given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[667,917,745,767]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" pagination="123 - 178" refId="ref119004" refString="Hartert, E. 1919 a. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. B. Types in the general collection. Novitates Zoologicae 26: 123 - 178." type="journal article" year="1919">Hartert (1919a: 171)</bibRefCitation>
is 24 April, whereas, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild, W." box="[667,930,774,796]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" pagination="59 - 83" refId="ref127068" refString="Rothschild, W. 1900. The avifauna of Laysan and the neighbouring islands: with a complete history to date of the birds of the Hawaiian possessions. Part 3. London: R. H. Porter, xx + 127 - 320, (Di) 1 - (Di) 21, pls. 59 - 83." type="journal article" year="1900">Rothschild (1900: 178</bibRefCitation>
, Di 19) said that the single male was shot by Wolstenholme on 20 April. Plate 65, reproduced on the cover of this bulletin, shows front and back views of this single specimen (
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild, W." box="[859,1112,893,915]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" pagination="59 - 83" refId="ref127068" refString="Rothschild, W. 1900. The avifauna of Laysan and the neighbouring islands: with a complete history to date of the birds of the Hawaiian possessions. Part 3. London: R. H. Porter, xx + 127 - 320, (Di) 1 - (Di) 21, pls. 59 - 83." type="journal article" year="1900">Rothschild, 1900: 178</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[667,1194,416,1391]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">
Palmer’s diary (
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild, W." box="[901,1114,923,945]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" pagination="59 - 83" refId="ref127068" refString="Rothschild, W. 1900. The avifauna of Laysan and the neighbouring islands: with a complete history to date of the birds of the Hawaiian possessions. Part 3. London: R. H. Porter, xx + 127 - 320, (Di) 1 - (Di) 21, pls. 59 - 83." type="journal article" year="1900">Rothschild, 1900</bibRefCitation>
: (Di)) indicates that he spent the period from 
<date pageId="30" pageNumber="30" value="1893-03-21" valueMax="1893-05-03" valueMin="1893-03-21">
21 March–3 May 
<quantity box="[845,900,982,1003]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.80822" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" unit="in" value="1893.0">1893</quantity>
</date>
in the Waialua district.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[667,1194,416,1391]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">
Beginning with 
<bibRefCitation author="Rothschild, W." box="[901,1188,1013,1035]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" pagination="59 - 83" refId="ref127068" refString="Rothschild, W. 1900. The avifauna of Laysan and the neighbouring islands: with a complete history to date of the birds of the Hawaiian possessions. Part 3. London: R. H. Porter, xx + 127 - 320, (Di) 1 - (Di) 21, pls. 59 - 83." type="journal article" year="1900">Rothschild (1900: 177)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[667,826,1042,1065]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Loxops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wolstenholmei">
<emphasis box="[667,826,1042,1065]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">wolstenholmei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bloxam, 1827" authorityName="Bloxam" authorityYear="1827" box="[766,1102,1071,1094]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Fringilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufa">
<emphasis box="[766,922,1071,1094]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">Fringilla rufa</emphasis>
Bloxam, 1827
</taxonomicName>
, but as Olson (1986: 148–149) showed, that name is a junior homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Wilson, 1811" authorityName="A. Wilson" authorityYear="1811" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Fringilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufa">
<emphasis box="[905,1058,1130,1153]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">Fringilla rufa</emphasis>
A. Wilson, 1811
</taxonomicName>
, which is in turn a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Merrem, 1786" authorityName="Merrem" authorityYear="1786" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Fringilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="iliaca">
<emphasis box="[1099,1193,1160,1183]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">F. iliaca</emphasis>
Merrem, 1786
</taxonomicName>
. As such Bloxam’s name is unavailable (ICZN, 1999: 59, Art. 57.2), and Rothschild’s name must be used. Also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Olson, S. L." box="[667,820,1279,1301]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref124372" refString="Olson, S. L. 1996. The contribution of the voyage of H. M. S. Blonde (1825) to Hawaiian ornithology. Archives of Natural History 23: 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1996">Olson (1996)</bibRefCitation>
for his discussion of Bloxam’s specimens from the voyage of H.M.S. 
<emphasis box="[1115,1194,1308,1331]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">Blonde</emphasis>
and publication of Bloxam’s notes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[667,1194,416,1391]" box="[696,998,1369,1391]" pageId="30" pageNumber="30">This subspecies is extinct.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
